    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1920-05-23T15:29:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1920-05-23T15:29:00-05:00" n="13"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d13">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">837.00/1670: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Chargé in Cuba</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">White</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Habana</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1920-05-23T15:00:00-05:29">
                            <hi rend="italic">May 23, 1920—3 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                        <lb/>[Received 4:59 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>117. Conservatives this morning nominated without opposition Rafael Montalvo as
                    presidential candidate. Selection of vice-president <pb facs="0103" n="13"
                        xml:id="pg_13"/> postponed pending agreement with Zayas coalitionists who
                    will probably be permitted to name candidate. Major Stephenson requests General
                    Crowder be notified.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">White</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
